      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">19.1506</ph> Women-Owned Small Business
Program sole source awards.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d1254e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1283e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> A contracting officer shall consider
a contract award to an EDWOSB concern on a sole source basis (see <xref href="6.302-5.dita#FAR_6_302_5"
                        base="i1119624"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">6.302-5</xref>(b)(7)) before
considering small business set-asides (see <xref href="19.203.dita#FAR_19_203"
                        base="i1101696"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.203</xref> and <xref href="Subpart_19.5.dita#FAR_Subpart_19_5"
                        base="i1100723"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpart  19.5</xref>) provided
none of the exclusions at <xref href="19.1504.dita#FAR_19_1504"
                        base="i1099222"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.1504</xref> apply
and-</p>
               <ol id="d1254e35" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1283e28" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> The acquisition is assigned a
NAICS code in which SBA has determined that WOSB concerns are underrepresented in
Federal procurement;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1283e33" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> The contracting
officer does not have a reasonable expectation that offers would
be received from two or more EDWOSB concerns; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1283e38" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> The conditions
in paragraph (c) of this section exist.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1283e43" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> A contracting
officer shall consider a contract award to a WOSB concern (including
EDWOSB concerns) eligible under the WOSB Program on a sole source
basis (see <xref href="6.302-5.dita#FAR_6_302_5"
                        base="i1119624"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">6.302-5</xref>(b)(7)) before
considering small business set-asides (see <xref href="19.203.dita#FAR_19_203"
                        base="i1101696"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.203</xref> and <xref href="Subpart_19.5.dita#FAR_Subpart_19_5"
                        base="i1100723"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpart  19.5</xref>) provided
none of the exclusions at <xref href="19.1504.dita#FAR_19_1504"
                        base="i1099222"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.1504</xref> apply
and-</p>
               <ol id="d1254e86" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1283e61" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> The acquisition is assigned a
NAICS code in which SBA has determined that WOSB concerns are substantially underrepresented
in Federal procurement;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1283e66" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> The contracting
officer does not have a reasonable expectation that offers would
be received from two or more WOSB concerns (including EDWOSB concerns);
and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1283e71" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> The conditions
in paragraph (c) of this section exist.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1283e76" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol id="d1254e125" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1283e81" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> The
anticipated award price of the contract, including options, will
not exceed-</p>
                     <ol id="d1254e135" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d1283e87" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              <ph rev="FAC 2021-01 October 2, 2020" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2019-013?>$7 million<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 19.1506 by—
a.  Removing from paragraph (c)(1)(i) “$6.5 million” and adding “$7 million” in its place; and 

?></ph> for a requirement
within the NAICS codes for manufacturing; or</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d1283e96" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              <ph rev="FAC 2021-01 October 2, 2020" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2019-013?>$4.5 million<?FM MARKER [Why] b.  Removing from paragraph (c)(1)(ii) “$4 million” and adding “$4.5 million” in its place.?></ph> for a
requirement within any other NAICS codes.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1283e105" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> The EDWOSB
concern or WOSB concern has been determined to be a responsible
contractor with respect to performance.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1283e110" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> The award
can be made at a fair and reasonable price.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1283e115" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph> The SBA
has the right to appeal the contracting officer’s decision not to
make a sole source award to either an EDWOSB concern or WOSB concern
eligible under the WOSB program.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
